<div id="header" class="flex-row prim-between sec-center mdl-button--raised">
  <div id="title">
    <img id="icon" src="~/sf/book.ico">
    <span>Scripture Forge</span>
  </div>
  <div>
    <a class="mdl-button mdl-button--raised mdl-button--colored mdl-button--accent" href="/account/register">
        Sign up
    </a>
    <a class="mdl-button mdl-button--raised" href="/account/login">
        Log in
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="content" class="flex-column prim-start sec-center"
 ngClass.lt-md="smallcontent" ngClass.md="mediumcontent" ngClass.gt-md="largecontent">
  <div id="welcome" class="flex-column prim-center sec-center">
      <h1>Welcome to Scripture Forge.</h1>
      <p>Work with your Scripture data in a web app giving you the option of engaging a wider variety of language speakers. The online Scripture Checking App can help you run a Scripture checking campaign with the aim of getting broader feedback to the translation team quickly.</p>
  </div>
  <div id="checking" class="flex-row prim-around sec-baseline">
    <div id="offline" class="text-column">
      <h4>Offline Capable</h4>
      <p>Users can connect once to get the scripture content on their device and then answer questions offline. Their answers can then be uploaded when they have internet again.</p>
    </div>
    <div id="paratext" class="text-column">
      <h4>Works with Paratext</h4>
      <p>Send/Receive with Paratext to get the project into Scripture Forge using your Paratext credentials. Update Paratext with the notes generated by the community checking collaborators.</p>
    </div>
    <div id="engagement" class="text-column">
      <h4>User Engagement</h4>
      <p>Turn on "invite a friend" to open up your campaign or keep feedback to a defined group. Users can answer questions, comment on other's answers, and +1 other's responses. Generate user engagement reports at the end of your campaign.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
